notes: Winkler|Many Paratrechina|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. notes: Bait|Paratrechina|Very still on the ridge. Little wind. Clear and sunny and dry all day. GigaPan (18*29) at Site 3. Not many large ambulatory ponerines visible all day (one in Active Search). Searched between 1100 and 1200m. Loads of bamboo between 1000 and 1100. Tapir dung along trail at 1000m. Can see station through the trees. Not a lot of visible ants. |IMG_4140.JPGhttp://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/42073/|

notes: Winkler|Into ethanol directly. Very rainy day. Myrmicinae|26mEPE|Waypoint 179||Late-ish start with Harry R. who needs to return by 2pm. Traps etc. out and open at 9:00am. Raining all morning with very strong gusting wind. Sifted fallen logs (Hypoponera-oids) and fallen canopy log for some `new` Doliochoderina. Video taken of the dominan Aphaenogaster taken at bait 4. Page 126 of book. 18.5C.|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66803/|http://bit.ly/e2DIex |http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|

notes: Sift|Pheidole, Attini, Paratrechina, Octostruma|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33|||http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Winkler|Many Paratrechina|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33|||http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Winkler|Many Paratrechina|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm.
